Diagram 1 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White's diagonal move at 1 is a deadly move. It aims at creating a snapback at \b\f1 A\b0\f0  and it is also a useful maek in removing eyespace.
\par
\par This results in black's death.
\par Even if black connects at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , black is still lifeless.
\par }
