Diagram 3 (Plausible?)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White's hane at 1 is intended to create a dead shape inside black's group. This seems plausible but after black 2 and 4 are played, it becomes apparent that there is no way to capture black now.
\par
\par If white descends at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , black captures at \b\f1 B\b0\f0  and lives.
\par }
